I need to identify the liabilities that are expected to be settled in the normal course of the entity's operating cycle.

Looking at the balance sheet, the line items that represent liabilities to be settled in the normal operating cycle are typically classified as current liabilities. In this balance sheet, "Total Current Liabilities" represents the sum of all such short-term obligations.

From the balance sheet:
- At the initial date (2023-12-31), the Total Current Liabilities amount is 0.00
- At the end date (2024-02-02), the Total Current Liabilities amount is 7605149.91

This represents the total of Accounts Payable (7566370.00) and Taxes Payable (38779.91), which are both expected to be settled in the normal course of operations.
